      <scopecontent id="aspace_c2114d8c9306537f82cb74e3d5b568a7">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>This collection contains business, family, and legal correspondence of plantation owner
            Dilmus Appleberry. It is largely composed of accounts, bills, invoices, indentures, and
            land surveys. Letters, some of a business nature, comprise about five percent of the
            collection. Correspondents whose names appear most often are Pettit and Leake, a legal
            firm of Goochland Court House; Atlantic and Virginia Fertilizing Company of Richmond,
            Virginia; and Dilmus Appleberry's nephew, Thomas A. Bledsoe.</p>
      </scopecontent>
